*Create GPG keypair:

gpg --full-generate-key
  - select:  (1) RSA and RSA
  - What keysize do you want? : 4096
  - 0 = key does not expire


_________________
*Steps to implementing GPG- create file

mkdir -p /home/tecviva/.secrets
chmod 700 /home/tecviva/.secrets

Create Key
echo "XXXXX" | gpg --armor --encrypt --recipient tecy > /home/tecviva/.secrets/tecbot_sdai.pass.gpg
chmod 600 /home/tecviva/.secrets/tecbot_sdai.pass.gpg

___________________
*Update Cache, so login info does not reset:

Cache limits to the GPG Password: 1 year
nano ~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf

default-cache-ttl 31536000
max-cache-ttl 31536000


Restart:

gpgconf --kill gpg-agent
gpgconf --launch gpg-agent


_________________________
*Check to see if GPG is unlocked:
gpg --quiet --batch --decrypt /home/tecviva/.secrets/tecbot_eth.pass.gpg > /dev/null

*If no prompt and exit code = 0 â†’ unlocked.
*If prompt for passphrase â†’ locked.

*Created script for easier view:
echo 'export GPG_TTY=$(tty)' >> ~/.bashrc
echo "alias gpgcheck='gpg --quiet --batch --decrypt /home/tecviva/.secrets/tecbot_eth.pass.gpg > /dev/null && echo \"âœ… GPG unlocked\" || echo \"ðŸ”’ GPG locked\"'" >> ~/.bashrc

*Use this command:
gpgcheck
